{{DISPLAYTITLE:CONFIG_PROTECT}}
<languages />

"CONFIG_PROTECT变量包含用空格分隔的目录列表，Portage不会盲目的拷贝新版本的文件到这些目录中，而是将这些目录中的文件当做配置文件，由用户手动检查更新是否需要和正确。"

The CONFIG_PROTECT variable is managed by Portage and contains entries from the users' [[profile]], system environment (which is often used by applications that update the variable through their {{Path|/etc/env.d}} file) and the users' {{Path|/etc/portage/make.conf}} setting.

For more information, see [http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=3&chap=2#doc_chap3 Configuration File Protect] in the Gentoo Handbook.

